{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Iterator","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The elements returned by this iterator","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"appear in the order that the tasks ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"completed"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not in the order that those tasks were added to the task group.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This iterator terminates after all tasks have completed successfully,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or after any task completes by throwing an error.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If a task completes by throwing an error,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it doesn’t return any further task results.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"After iterating over the results of each task,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it’s valid to make a new iterator for the task group,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which you can use to iterate over the results of new tasks you add to the group.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can also make a new iterator to resume iteration","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after a child task throws an error.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["group.addTask { 1 }","group.addTask { throw SomeError }","group.addTask { 2 }","","do {","    \/\/ Assuming the child tasks complete in order, this prints \"1\"","    \/\/ and then throws an error.","    for try await r in group { print(r) }","} catch {","    \/\/ Resolve the error.","}","","\/\/ Assuming the child tasks complete in order, this prints \"2\".","for try await r in group { print(r) }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"name":"See Also","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ThrowingTaskGroup.next()"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:Scg8IteratorV","title":"ThrowingTaskGroup.Iterator","roleHeading":"Structure","platforms":[{"name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"8.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"iPadOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"8.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"Mac Catalyst","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"10.10","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"tvOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"9.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"visionOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"1.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"watchOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"2.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Iterator"}],"symbolKind":"struct","role":"symbol","conformance":{"availabilityPrefix":[{"text":"Available when","type":"text"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"text":"Conforms when","type":"text"}],"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ChildTaskResult"},{"text":" conforms to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Failure"},{"text":" conforms to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Error"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Iterator"}],"extendedModule":"_Concurrency","modules":[{"name":"Swift","relatedModules":[]}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","doc:\/\/com.appl